definitions.definition: A launch or ascent into the air or into flight , such as of an aircraft , rocket , bird , high-jumper etc.
examples: That high-jumper's takeoff needs some work.
The mute swan, being one of the world's heaviest flying birds, can have a laborious takeoff .

definitions.definition: A parody or lampoon of someone or something.
examples: Weird Al 's song "Lasagna" is a takeoff on the popular song "La Bamba".

definitions.definition: A quantification , especially of building materials .
The removal of sheets from the press .
The spot from which one takes off ; specifically, the place from which a jumper rises in leaping .
The initial movement a surfer makes to start riding a wave.
